'''síma''' or '''isima''' means "mind, imagination, conception" in [[Quenya]]<ref>{{VT|49}}, p.16</ref>
==Etymology==
Perhaps a possible [[PQ]] [[Sundocarmë|Root]] *I-SIM or *SÍ.

It is not clear whether it contains the ending ''[[-ma]]'' (''sí-ma'') or if ''m'' is a part of the root (''sím-a'').
==Other forms==
*'''símaryassen''' "in their conception"
